<h1>Privacy Policy - Man Down</h1>
<p><strong>Last update:</strong> March 2026</p>

<div class="section">
<h2>Introduction</h2>
<p>
This Privacy Policy describes how the Man Down application processes and protects user data when installed on devices compatible with the Garmin Connect IQ platform.
</p>
<p>
The application provides a Man-Down monitoring system designed to detect falls or emergency situations and to notify a remote monitoring operator.
</p>
<p>
The system has been designed according to privacy by design and data minimization principles, in line with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).
</p>
</div>

<div class="section">
<h2>Data Collected</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Motion data:</strong> Accelerometer measurements</li>
<li><strong>Physiological data:</strong> Heart rate</li>
<li><strong>Location data:</strong> GPS position</li>
<li><strong>Device-related data:</strong> Device identifier</li>
<li><strong>Application status data:</strong> Monitoring status, alarm status, system diagnostic information</li>
</ul>

<p>The application does not collect personal identifiers such as:</p>
<ul>
<li>Name</li>
<li>Email address</li>
<li>Phone number</li>
<li>Contacts</li>
<li>Calendar information</li>
</ul>
</div>

<div class="section">
<h2>Purpose of Data Processing</h2>
<ul>
<li>Detection of potential critical events (fall/prolonged immobility)</li>
<li>Monitoring of abnormal physiological conditions</li>
<li>Emergency alert management</li>
<li>Transmission of emergency information to a monitoring service</li>
<li>System validation and performance optimization, only where explicitly consented by the user</li>
</ul>

<p>Data are not used for advertising, marketing, or user profiling.</p>
</div>

<div class="section">
<h2>Data Transmission</h2>
<p>
Some data may be transmitted from the smartwatch, through the Garmin Connect mobile application, to a remote server infrastructure.
</p>

<ul>
<li>Device identifier</li>
<li>GPS location</li>
<li>Heart rate</li>
<li>Monitoring status</li>
<li>Alarm events</li>
</ul>

<p>
Accelerometer data may be transmitted for algorithm validation purposes only where the user has explicitly provided consent.
</p>

<p>
All communications are performed using secure network protocols (TLS/HTTPS).
</p>
</div>

<div class="section">
<h2>Local Data Storage</h2>
<p>
The application performs limited local persistent storage only when data transmission to the remote server is not successful.
</p>

<ul>
<li>Undelivered event messages</li>
</ul>

<p>
Data are automatically deleted once successfully transmitted and are not stored continuously or redundantly.
</p>
</div>

<div class="section">
<h2>Remote Data Processing</h2>
<p>
When the system is connected to the internet via the Garmin Connect mobile application, selected data may be transmitted to a remote server to support:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Emergency monitoring</li>
<li>Incident analysis</li>
<li>System performance improvement (only where explicitly consented by the user)</li>
</ul>

<p>
Location data may be periodically acquired and transmitted by the application to maintain an up-to-date estimate of the user’s position.
</p>

<p>
This approach allows the system to provide the most accurate available location in the event of a detected fall or a manually triggered SOS alert, including scenarios where a real-time GPS fix may not be immediately available.
</p>

<p>
Outside emergency conditions, location data are transmitted but not persistently stored or further processed, and are not used for tracking or profiling purposes.
</p>

<p>
Persistent storage and processing of location data occur only in relation to confirmed emergency events.
</p>

<p>
Access to monitoring data is restricted to authorized personnel.
</p>
</div>

<div class="section">
<h2>Data Security</h2>
<ul>
<li>Encrypted communication channels (HTTPS/TLS)</li>
<li>Access control mechanisms</li>
<li>Data minimization principles</li>
</ul>
</div>

<div class="section">
<h2>User Rights</h2>
<ul>
<li>Access to their data</li>
<li>Deletion of stored data</li>
<li>Withdrawal of consent for optional data processing</li>
</ul>

<p>
Requests can be sent to the contact address listed below.
</p>
</div>

